1
00:02:51,920 --> 00:02:53,160
My son.

2
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:00,680
Please don't call me that.

3
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:11,880
I was wrong. I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

4
00:03:21,520 --> 00:03:24,200
I… I really regret it.

5
00:03:33,320 --> 00:03:34,880
It's okay, Mr. Sarut.

6
00:03:37,840 --> 00:03:39,720
You don't have to regret anything.

7
00:03:41,720 --> 00:03:43,040
I won't be angry at you

8
00:03:43,760 --> 00:03:45,360
for what you've done.

9
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:49,400
I won't hate you.

10
00:03:54,280 --> 00:03:56,200
I will respect you

11
00:03:57,040 --> 00:03:58,400
as an elder.

12
00:04:05,160 --> 00:04:07,160
But I will never forget

13
00:04:09,120 --> 00:04:10,480
how much your choice…

14
00:04:14,240 --> 00:04:16,000
hurt me.

15
00:04:17,560 --> 00:04:20,720
I'm sorry. I really regret it, son.

16
00:04:26,760 --> 00:04:29,720
You know what? I just realized

17
00:04:32,960 --> 00:04:34,760
that when you abandoned me,

18
00:04:36,640 --> 00:04:37,760
I was just

19
00:04:38,280 --> 00:04:41,040
a child who couldn't even speak yet.

20
00:04:42,680 --> 00:04:44,560
How could you do that?

21
00:04:47,240 --> 00:04:50,000
I'm sorry. I really regret it.

22
00:04:51,920 --> 00:04:53,600
Please forgive me.

23
00:04:56,960 --> 00:05:00,200
I think today,
you've already received what you deserve.

24
00:05:03,320 --> 00:05:04,560
Let's go, Kluay.

25
00:05:05,280 --> 00:05:09,160
Warat. Son.

26
00:05:09,680 --> 00:05:12,840
Can you hear me? I'm sorry!

27
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:37,960
ONE MONTH LATER

28
00:06:06,240 --> 00:06:07,480
Mom…

29
00:06:09,440 --> 00:06:10,400
Did you find her?

30
00:06:13,280 --> 00:06:14,880
Since that day…

31
00:06:23,280 --> 00:06:24,960
I love you, honey.

32
00:06:26,080 --> 00:06:28,320
…I haven't seen anything anymore.

33
00:06:29,840 --> 00:06:31,280
What do you mean?

34
00:06:32,920 --> 00:06:36,200
I don't see spirits, signs,

35
00:06:36,920 --> 00:06:38,720
anything at all.

36
00:06:41,520 --> 00:06:42,720
Isn't that a good thing?

37
00:06:43,720 --> 00:06:45,840
You won't have to see
anything scary anymore.

38
00:06:48,240 --> 00:06:49,640
What's wrong?

39
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:55,080
I thought I'd get another chance
to talk to my mom.

40
00:06:58,640 --> 00:06:59,840
It's okay.

41
00:07:01,080 --> 00:07:03,520
Just because we can't see something
doesn't mean it doesn't exist.

42
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:07,280
I believe she's watching over us…

43
00:07:08,880 --> 00:07:10,000
with love.

44
00:07:14,240 --> 00:07:18,160
Do you think the reason I saw those signs
was because of her?

45
00:07:20,880 --> 00:07:23,240
I believe she's always protecting us

46
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:26,080
and guiding us back to each other.

47
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:42,040
Thank you

48
00:07:42,120 --> 00:07:44,040
for always being by my side.

49
00:07:45,880 --> 00:07:46,960
Come here.

50
00:07:56,480 --> 00:07:57,840
You want me to sit here?

51
00:08:01,840 --> 00:08:04,400
At first, I thought after all this,
I would transfer

52
00:08:04,480 --> 00:08:05,600
all the Vanich shares to you.

53
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:07,640
Oh no, that's not necessary.

54
00:08:07,720 --> 00:08:09,800
Even if I had them,
I wouldn't know what to do anyway.

55
00:08:10,840 --> 00:08:13,320
But I've decided. I won't transfer them.

56
00:08:14,080 --> 00:08:15,880
- I'll use this method instead.
- Hm?

57
00:08:22,760 --> 00:08:24,000
Will you marry me?

58
00:08:30,080 --> 00:08:31,160
Yes.

59
00:08:31,880 --> 00:08:33,400
Why did you answer so quickly?

60
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:34,799
I don't need to think.

61
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:36,440
Aren't you going to play hard to get?

62
00:08:36,520 --> 00:08:38,159
No way.

63
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:39,640
Okay, good.

64
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:30,280
Kluay…

65
00:09:30,360 --> 00:09:31,360
What, Som?

66
00:09:31,960 --> 00:09:34,400
Why are you so beautiful?

67
00:09:35,640 --> 00:09:38,680
Maybe because I have a personal stylist.

68
00:09:38,760 --> 00:09:41,080
We've grown up together
since we were born.

69
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:46,800
Soon you'll be living at Vanich House.

70
00:09:46,880 --> 00:09:49,040
You'll be both Mrs. Wanee's granddaughter

71
00:09:49,120 --> 00:09:51,360
and Mr. Warat's wife.

72
00:09:52,840 --> 00:09:57,120
So who are Mama Toi and I
supposed to stay with?

73
00:09:57,720 --> 00:10:01,400
Hey, why are you saying it like
I won't come back to Baan Saeng?

74
00:10:01,920 --> 00:10:03,640
I just feel lonely.

75
00:10:03,720 --> 00:10:06,120
- We've never been apart before.
- Mm.

76
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:08,360
Now you're complaining?

77
00:10:09,160 --> 00:10:13,400
Have you and Mr. Arnon
talked about marriage yet?

78
00:10:15,560 --> 00:10:17,040
Well,

79
00:10:17,120 --> 00:10:19,000
he's mentioned it,

80
00:10:19,080 --> 00:10:20,360
but…

81
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:22,200
But?

82
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:28,440
He keeps saying,
"Let me save money first."

83
00:10:28,520 --> 00:10:32,680
I don't understand.
I don't care where or how we get married.

84
00:10:32,760 --> 00:10:35,080
I don't understand what he's thinking.

85
00:10:35,680 --> 00:10:37,440
You said that yourself. Anywhere is fine?

86
00:10:37,520 --> 00:10:39,440
- Yes, I'm ready right now.
- Mm.

87
00:10:41,680 --> 00:10:42,520
Grandma.

88
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:47,880
Som, come outside. I need to talk to you.

89
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:12,840
Arnon?

90
00:11:18,880 --> 00:11:21,240
Why are you wearing this?

91
00:11:33,120 --> 00:11:34,360
What is this?

92
00:11:35,120 --> 00:11:36,400
Will you marry me?

93
00:11:38,120 --> 00:11:39,360
Marry?

94
00:11:40,240 --> 00:11:41,320
Where?

95
00:11:41,400 --> 00:11:42,680
Right here.

96
00:11:44,960 --> 00:11:47,600
No, I haven't told Mama Toi yet.

97
00:11:48,880 --> 00:11:50,520
I already know.

98
00:11:51,520 --> 00:11:54,000
Mom? Grandpa?

99
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:04,120
Mr. Warat? Kluay?

100
00:12:05,520 --> 00:12:06,840
Everyone…

101
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,080
Who planned this?

102
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:10,920
Well…

103
00:12:11,800 --> 00:12:17,280
Mr. Warat, Ms. Kluay,
this is the venue for the wedding.

104
00:12:17,360 --> 00:12:19,920
We're planning a seaside wedding.

105
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:21,320
- Listen to him.
- Alright.

106
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:25,520
Here, this is the location.
I've checked it already.

107
00:12:25,600 --> 00:12:28,280
- Wow.
- Yeah.

108
00:12:28,360 --> 00:12:30,640
It's beautiful. I like it. Do you?

109
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:32,320
- Very much.
- Wow.

110
00:12:32,840 --> 00:12:35,040
And here's the food.
There are many options.

111
00:12:35,120 --> 00:12:38,440
They're very generous with the menu.
And this…

112
00:12:38,520 --> 00:12:43,120
This will be the photo backdrop area.

113
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:46,000
Alright? It'll be gorgeous. Next.

114
00:12:46,080 --> 00:12:47,840
This one is the groom's suit.

115
00:12:47,920 --> 00:12:50,680
- Here.
- Wow!

116
00:12:50,760 --> 00:12:52,560
And this is the bride's dress.

117
00:12:54,640 --> 00:12:56,800
Since when

118
00:12:56,880 --> 00:12:59,480
did you become a wedding planning guru?

119
00:13:00,160 --> 00:13:01,120
You're really good at this.

120
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:02,200
Oh.

121
00:13:02,720 --> 00:13:05,640
- Actually, I just wanted to…
- Mm.

122
00:13:05,720 --> 00:13:07,360
- …go there…
- But I think

123
00:13:07,440 --> 00:13:09,880
this dress suits Som more.

124
00:13:10,400 --> 00:13:13,280
If she wore it as a bride,

125
00:13:13,360 --> 00:13:15,040
she'd look so beautiful.

126
00:13:20,560 --> 00:13:22,080
- Hey, hey.
- So this is not…

127
00:13:22,160 --> 00:13:24,440
This dress is not for me.

128
00:13:25,320 --> 00:13:26,560
- He's blushing.
- Mm.

129
00:13:26,640 --> 00:13:31,360
Actually, I've always wanted
to marry Som by the sea too.

130
00:13:31,440 --> 00:13:33,480
But there's just one problem.

131
00:13:33,560 --> 00:13:34,680
I ran out of money.

132
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:38,120
Don't tell me…

133
00:13:38,640 --> 00:13:41,760
Mr. Warat knew, Kluay knew, everyone knew?

134
00:13:42,440 --> 00:13:43,800
All the guests knew too.

135
00:13:43,880 --> 00:13:47,400
And I'm the only one who didn't?
Why didn't you tell me?

136
00:13:47,480 --> 00:13:49,040
It's a surprise!

137
00:13:49,680 --> 00:13:50,840
Is this really okay?

138
00:13:58,520 --> 00:14:00,720
Why are you so mad at me?

139
00:14:00,800 --> 00:14:02,120
Because you…

140
00:14:07,040 --> 00:14:09,400
Why didn't you tell me first?

141
00:14:09,480 --> 00:14:10,880
I could've dieted and prepared.

142
00:14:10,960 --> 00:14:13,520
What if I can't even fit into the dress?

143
00:14:13,600 --> 00:14:14,480
You know what?

144
00:14:15,040 --> 00:14:17,680
No matter what,
you're always beautiful to me.

145
00:14:19,920 --> 00:14:21,240
Arnon…

146
00:14:24,880 --> 00:14:25,960
Som.

147
00:14:26,880 --> 00:14:28,840
- Go after her.
- Good luck!

148
00:14:34,400 --> 00:14:38,160
So Mrs. Wanee, you have to be
the elder for both sides.

149
00:14:38,240 --> 00:14:39,480
Oh, right.

150
00:14:39,560 --> 00:14:41,120
I'll be happy to.

151
00:14:41,200 --> 00:14:42,600
But still…

152
00:14:42,680 --> 00:14:47,040
I must thank you, Mrs. Toi,
for raising Kluay so well.

153
00:14:47,120 --> 00:14:51,840
Oh, I have to say that Kluay
is such a lovely child.

154
00:14:52,360 --> 00:14:54,400
- She's always been a good girl.
- Mm.

155
00:14:54,480 --> 00:14:58,360
She never once wanted something
that didn't belong to her.

156
00:14:58,440 --> 00:15:01,040
Kluay is patient,

157
00:15:01,120 --> 00:15:04,600
hardworking, and incredibly strong-minded.

158
00:15:04,680 --> 00:15:10,560
I never thought
I'd be lucky enough to meet Kluay again.

159
00:15:11,600 --> 00:15:18,280
And I feel twice as lucky
to have met you too.

160
00:15:18,360 --> 00:15:22,760
And from everything I've seen,

161
00:15:22,840 --> 00:15:25,040
Kluay has always been
a kind-hearted child.

162
00:15:25,120 --> 00:15:27,400
Most importantly, everyone loves her.

163
00:15:30,360 --> 00:15:32,080
- Mrs. Wanee.
- Yes?

164
00:15:32,840 --> 00:15:36,440
Even though I'm not Kluay's real mother…

165
00:15:36,520 --> 00:15:39,360
Oh my, why did you say that?

166
00:15:39,880 --> 00:15:43,400
But I love her
as if she were my own daughter.

167
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:45,440
Yes.

168
00:15:45,520 --> 00:15:51,280
Let's just say that the two of us
love and cherish these two children

169
00:15:51,360 --> 00:15:54,560
as if they were our own.

170
00:15:54,640 --> 00:15:55,880
Right?

171
00:15:57,080 --> 00:15:58,280
Well…

172
00:15:58,360 --> 00:16:03,360
Ms. Ampha and Mr. Wichan
must finally be able to rest in peace now.

173
00:16:03,440 --> 00:16:04,640
Yes.

174
00:16:05,160 --> 00:16:07,280
It has to be that way.

175
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:10,240
- Let's go.
- Yes.

176
00:16:11,480 --> 00:16:13,880
I'm so happy today.

177
00:16:18,320 --> 00:16:19,160
Oh dear.

178
00:16:19,240 --> 00:16:21,200
Will I make it in time? I'm going first.

179
00:16:21,280 --> 00:16:22,480
Slow down, Som.

180
00:16:22,560 --> 00:16:24,840
Ah!

181
00:16:26,400 --> 00:16:28,040
You both look beautiful today.

182
00:16:28,120 --> 00:16:29,960
- Thank you.
- Grandpa.

183
00:16:30,040 --> 00:16:30,920
Oh.

184
00:16:32,760 --> 00:16:35,280
Grandpa, I want to
talk to you about something.

185
00:16:36,080 --> 00:16:37,120
Let's go.

186
00:16:40,680 --> 00:16:41,560
Grandpa,

187
00:16:42,240 --> 00:16:46,320
ever since that day,
I haven't seen Mom again.

188
00:16:46,840 --> 00:16:48,200
And do you see…?

189
00:16:48,280 --> 00:16:50,160
I can't see them anymore.

190
00:16:50,240 --> 00:16:53,040
Now I see everything like a normal person.

191
00:16:54,040 --> 00:16:56,480
That's probably
because of your mother's power.

192
00:16:57,240 --> 00:16:58,600
Mom's power?

193
00:16:58,680 --> 00:17:00,000
Yes. Power.

194
00:17:00,760 --> 00:17:02,800
Her desire to protect you.

195
00:17:02,880 --> 00:17:06,160
The attachment she still had, the reason
she couldn't leave this world behind,

196
00:17:06,760 --> 00:17:10,880
made Mr. Ampha try to find
a way to communicate with you.

197
00:17:10,960 --> 00:17:13,280
That's why you were
able to see the afterlife.

198
00:17:14,520 --> 00:17:16,400
The afterlife?

199
00:17:16,480 --> 00:17:17,440
Yes.

200
00:17:17,960 --> 00:17:20,440
But now that everything has been resolved,

201
00:17:20,520 --> 00:17:21,880
and you're safe,

202
00:17:22,400 --> 00:17:24,480
Ms. Ampha no longer
has anything to worry about.

203
00:17:26,319 --> 00:17:27,880
So that's why

204
00:17:27,960 --> 00:17:31,200
I can't see the afterlife anymore?

205
00:17:31,280 --> 00:17:32,520
Yes.

206
00:17:33,040 --> 00:17:35,440
Because you already know
everything you need to know.

207
00:17:35,960 --> 00:17:39,000
There's no reason anymore
for you to see things you shouldn't.

208
00:17:39,920 --> 00:17:41,840
That's simply how nature works.

209
00:17:43,640 --> 00:17:45,400
Then,

210
00:17:46,240 --> 00:17:48,680
will I ever see Mom again?

211
00:17:49,720 --> 00:17:51,640
Your mother is always with you.

212
00:17:52,160 --> 00:17:54,920
In who you are, in every breath you take.

213
00:17:55,600 --> 00:17:58,560
In your thoughts, in everything you do.

214
00:17:59,160 --> 00:18:02,440
I just wanted to thank her myself.

215
00:18:05,360 --> 00:18:07,400
What does it mean
that you can't see her anymore?

216
00:18:09,600 --> 00:18:10,440
Hm?

217
00:18:11,040 --> 00:18:13,480
It means she has no more worries left.

218
00:18:13,560 --> 00:18:16,080
But you can still thank her.

219
00:18:17,760 --> 00:18:19,240
Be happy.

220
00:18:19,320 --> 00:18:23,200
And create happiness for yourself
and the people around you every day.

221
00:18:24,240 --> 00:18:27,400
There is nothing parents want more

222
00:18:28,160 --> 00:18:31,280
than seeing their child
happy every single day.

223
00:18:35,480 --> 00:18:37,560
Thank you, Grandpa.

224
00:18:38,960 --> 00:18:40,960
Your mom doesn't have to worry anymore.

225
00:18:44,280 --> 00:18:45,600
Thank you, Mom.

226
00:19:42,080 --> 00:19:43,440
You're here?

227
00:19:44,640 --> 00:19:46,520
Sorry I'm late.

228
00:19:51,320 --> 00:19:53,800
I thought you'd arrive before me.

229
00:19:56,800 --> 00:19:59,320
I had a few things to take care of.

230
00:20:01,680 --> 00:20:03,000
I've missed you.

231
00:20:04,760 --> 00:20:06,120
I've missed you all along.

232
00:20:07,920 --> 00:20:10,120
I've missed you too.

233
00:20:14,320 --> 00:20:16,800
There's nothing left
to worry about anymore.

234
00:20:22,600 --> 00:20:24,040
Have some tea.

235
00:20:26,040 --> 00:20:28,920
You have so many things to tell me.

236
00:20:53,920 --> 00:20:56,160
- Do I look handsome yet, Mr. Warat?
- Not yet.

237
00:20:56,240 --> 00:20:59,600
Hey, why would you say that?

238
00:21:01,120 --> 00:21:02,160
Can you fix it?

239
00:21:03,960 --> 00:21:06,560
If you want to look more handsome,
go get plastic surgery.

240
00:21:06,640 --> 00:21:08,880
You've gone this far,

241
00:21:09,400 --> 00:21:10,800
you might as well go all the way
to see a doctor!

242
00:21:15,680 --> 00:21:17,200
Looks like this lady's period hasn't come.

243
00:21:18,240 --> 00:21:19,880
Try looking in the mirror.

244
00:21:22,040 --> 00:21:23,240
Handsome?

245
00:21:24,280 --> 00:21:26,720
Well, of course.
I'm the only one in the mirror.

246
00:21:26,800 --> 00:21:30,480
Exactly. That's what a life partner is.

247
00:21:33,200 --> 00:21:36,320
What? Are you flirting with me?

248
00:21:37,760 --> 00:21:38,640
Dummy.

249
00:21:39,320 --> 00:21:40,640
I mean

250
00:21:40,720 --> 00:21:43,000
since you're the only one in the mirror,
of course you'll look handsome.

251
00:21:43,080 --> 00:21:45,760
That's what having a life partner is like.

252
00:21:46,880 --> 00:21:49,040
<i>Marriage means making a choice,</i>

253
00:21:49,840 --> 00:21:51,560
<i>and once you choose,</i>
<i>there are no other options left.</i>

254
00:21:52,760 --> 00:21:54,240
<i>We stay together.</i>

255
00:21:55,480 --> 00:21:57,560
<i>We may be born differently,</i>

256
00:21:59,280 --> 00:22:02,320
<i>we may disagree sometimes, that's normal.</i>

257
00:22:03,520 --> 00:22:05,240
<i>But as long as</i>
<i>we never look at anyone else,</i>

258
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:07,760
<i>the person standing in front of us</i>

259
00:22:07,840 --> 00:22:10,400
<i>will always be good enough</i>
<i>and important enough.</i>

260
00:22:14,360 --> 00:22:17,080
So are you the groom

261
00:22:17,160 --> 00:22:19,840
or the wedding elder?
You're nagging so much.

262
00:22:21,800 --> 00:22:23,720
If my father were still alive,

263
00:22:24,640 --> 00:22:26,200
he'd definitely sound just like you.

264
00:22:26,880 --> 00:22:28,160
And why do you think that?

265
00:22:29,880 --> 00:22:32,680
Because that's the only reason my father

266
00:22:35,240 --> 00:22:36,560
stayed loyal to one woman.

267
00:22:43,960 --> 00:22:46,400
With the utmost respect, Mr. Warat.

268
00:22:46,920 --> 00:22:49,440
Everything is ready now.

269
00:22:58,280 --> 00:23:02,520
Hello, everyone, I'm Arnon.
I'll be the MC for this wedding.

270
00:23:03,120 --> 00:23:06,680
As everyone already knows,
though I only just found out,

271
00:23:06,760 --> 00:23:09,560
today I'm also the MC

272
00:23:09,640 --> 00:23:11,720
and the bride too.

273
00:23:13,680 --> 00:23:18,960
And now, everyone,
please welcome the bride and groom.

274
00:23:37,960 --> 00:23:39,040
Kluay.

275
00:23:41,120 --> 00:23:42,840
Please stay with me for a very long time.

276
00:23:45,200 --> 00:23:46,280
Yes.

277
00:23:47,880 --> 00:23:49,120
I love you.

278
00:23:51,360 --> 00:23:53,280
I love you too.

279
00:24:15,760 --> 00:24:16,680
Yay!

280
00:24:37,440 --> 00:24:38,600
I love you, Som.

281
00:24:40,120 --> 00:24:41,560
I love you too.

282
00:24:55,200 --> 00:24:56,560
Kiss.

283
00:25:27,360 --> 00:25:28,520
Why are you bowing to me?

284
00:25:29,560 --> 00:25:31,640
I came to apologize to you, Dad.

285
00:25:32,280 --> 00:25:33,520
Who's your dad?

286
00:25:36,480 --> 00:25:37,880
Get out of here.

287
00:25:38,400 --> 00:25:39,440
Leave.

288
00:25:39,960 --> 00:25:42,120
Don't come ruining
other people's happy occasion.

289
00:25:42,960 --> 00:25:44,480
I'm sorry, Dad,

290
00:25:45,360 --> 00:25:47,360
for what Ameena and I did.

291
00:25:47,440 --> 00:25:49,400
It really was necessary.

292
00:25:50,840 --> 00:25:53,360
Necessary? What's necessary?

293
00:25:53,880 --> 00:25:57,400
What could possibly matter more
to her than the father sitting right here?

294
00:26:00,000 --> 00:26:01,760
"What meaning does family have

295
00:26:02,520 --> 00:26:04,440
if it isn't built from love?"

296
00:26:06,520 --> 00:26:08,520
What nonsense are you rambling about?

297
00:26:09,400 --> 00:26:11,160
Ameena said this to me

298
00:26:11,960 --> 00:26:13,560
when she was pregnant with our child.

299
00:26:14,320 --> 00:26:15,520
Your child?

300
00:26:16,040 --> 00:26:16,960
Yes.

301
00:26:18,040 --> 00:26:19,440
Your grandchild.

302
00:26:20,200 --> 00:26:21,600
Then why didn't she come with you?

303
00:26:21,680 --> 00:26:23,360
Ameena has to stay
and take care of the baby.

304
00:26:24,200 --> 00:26:25,760
The baby isn't very healthy.

305
00:26:27,320 --> 00:26:30,840
The doctor said it was because of
the mother's stress hormones

306
00:26:30,920 --> 00:26:32,480
that the baby turned out this way.

307
00:26:33,480 --> 00:26:36,480
So this is how you've been
taking care of my daughter?

308
00:26:37,640 --> 00:26:38,960
I'm sorry, Dad.

309
00:26:39,040 --> 00:26:41,680
I really did my best.

310
00:26:41,760 --> 00:26:44,480
But Ameena was under a lot of stress,

311
00:26:44,560 --> 00:26:46,920
and she worried constantly

312
00:26:47,000 --> 00:26:48,680
even if she looked normal on the outside.

313
00:26:53,160 --> 00:26:55,040
Take me to see Ameena.

314
00:26:56,560 --> 00:26:57,760
Yes, Dad.

315
00:26:58,720 --> 00:27:02,160
As for the wedding,
we'll talk about it again

316
00:27:02,240 --> 00:27:03,760
once my grandchild gets better.

317
00:27:17,880 --> 00:27:20,480
Thank you for coming
to the wedding, Mr. Sarut.

318
00:27:22,160 --> 00:27:23,400
Congratulations.

319
00:27:26,240 --> 00:27:28,560
I'm sorry
about what happened in your family.

320
00:27:36,960 --> 00:27:38,120
I'm the one

321
00:27:39,960 --> 00:27:41,280
who should apologize.

322
00:27:43,040 --> 00:27:44,320
It's alright.

323
00:27:45,480 --> 00:27:47,440
You were a victim too.

324
00:27:51,400 --> 00:27:54,160
If only I hadn't been so greedy,

325
00:27:55,000 --> 00:27:56,200
things might have been better.

326
00:28:10,480 --> 00:28:13,040
So, how is Ms. Anong?

327
00:28:15,800 --> 00:28:16,880
Anong…

328
00:28:34,560 --> 00:28:36,720
Who brought all these things
for the patient?

329
00:28:37,720 --> 00:28:39,720
Oh, the doctor already allowed it.

330
00:28:40,360 --> 00:28:41,640
Why?

331
00:28:41,720 --> 00:28:44,280
Because it helps calm the patient down.

332
00:29:06,320 --> 00:29:07,880
Mr. Rut,

333
00:29:09,120 --> 00:29:11,200
I made soup for you.

334
00:29:11,720 --> 00:29:13,480
It's still hot.

335
00:29:14,120 --> 00:29:16,160
Please have some.

336
00:29:18,160 --> 00:29:19,520
That's good.

337
00:29:25,640 --> 00:29:27,000
Eat a little more.

338
00:29:27,880 --> 00:29:29,400
Okay. Thank you.

339
00:29:44,200 --> 00:29:45,240
Anong.

340
00:30:00,440 --> 00:30:03,160
Sin! Sin.

341
00:30:03,240 --> 00:30:05,520
Sin, it's really you.

342
00:30:06,240 --> 00:30:07,520
You're not dead.

343
00:30:07,600 --> 00:30:10,560
I knew it. I knew you weren't dead.

344
00:30:11,440 --> 00:30:13,800
You ran away, didn't you?

345
00:30:17,600 --> 00:30:18,720
Sin.

346
00:30:21,120 --> 00:30:25,000
Sin, take me away with you.

347
00:30:25,080 --> 00:30:27,080
Let's escape together.

348
00:30:28,120 --> 00:30:30,600
Then we'll go kill Warat.

349
00:30:32,160 --> 00:30:36,200
We'll take back everything
that should belong to us.

350
00:30:36,920 --> 00:30:38,880
Alright, Sin?

351
00:30:38,960 --> 00:30:39,840
Anong.

352
00:30:46,040 --> 00:30:48,080
Sin, why are you calling me that?

353
00:30:50,200 --> 00:30:53,280
There's nothing that belongs to us, Anong.

354
00:30:59,680 --> 00:31:00,640
If they…

355
00:31:02,600 --> 00:31:03,560
If they…

356
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:09,040
If they hadn't taken Na's family away,

357
00:31:11,800 --> 00:31:16,120
none of this would've happened. Na… Na…

358
00:31:17,040 --> 00:31:18,560
Na…

359
00:31:20,080 --> 00:31:23,880
Na, I really did everything I could.

360
00:31:23,960 --> 00:31:25,960
I really tried my best.

361
00:31:26,040 --> 00:31:28,600
I tried my best.

362
00:31:29,480 --> 00:31:30,640
Na,

363
00:31:32,400 --> 00:31:35,240
I thought things would get better

364
00:31:36,320 --> 00:31:38,360
once Lakkana grew up.

365
00:31:43,360 --> 00:31:45,640
I thought I'd stop then.

366
00:31:47,960 --> 00:31:50,000
But they never stopped!

367
00:31:50,080 --> 00:31:52,440
- They never stopped!
- Nong, calm down.

368
00:31:52,520 --> 00:31:55,520
They took Lakkana away.

369
00:31:59,600 --> 00:32:02,760
Why? Why?

370
00:32:02,840 --> 00:32:04,920
Why do poor people

371
00:32:05,600 --> 00:32:09,480
always have to be the ones who give in,
the ones beneath everyone else,

372
00:32:09,560 --> 00:32:11,080
the pathetic ones?

373
00:32:11,160 --> 00:32:13,640
Why do rich people
get to have everything?!

374
00:32:13,720 --> 00:32:16,880
It has nothing to do
with being rich or poor, Anong.

375
00:32:19,200 --> 00:32:20,280
It's about conscience.

376
00:32:22,480 --> 00:32:23,880
About right and wrong.

377
00:32:24,520 --> 00:32:26,080
Greed and the things people choose to do.

378
00:32:27,680 --> 00:32:28,600
Anong,

379
00:32:29,120 --> 00:32:31,480
none of this belongs to us.

380
00:32:33,600 --> 00:32:36,440
There's nothing honorable
about taking what belongs to someone else.

381
00:32:39,600 --> 00:32:41,280
Stealing from other people,

382
00:32:41,360 --> 00:32:43,280
using other people's wealth.

383
00:32:44,600 --> 00:32:47,520
That's no different from being a thief.

384
00:32:51,800 --> 00:32:53,080
You thief!

385
00:32:54,080 --> 00:32:55,400
Sarut.

386
00:32:55,480 --> 00:32:56,680
You filthy thief.

387
00:32:57,200 --> 00:33:00,400
Go! You filthy thief!

388
00:33:01,760 --> 00:33:02,680
Well, I think

389
00:33:03,480 --> 00:33:05,600
we should stop talking about the past.

390
00:33:06,560 --> 00:33:07,520
Alright?

391
00:33:08,760 --> 00:33:12,840
Anyway, how's Kluay doing? Is she alright?

392
00:33:14,040 --> 00:33:16,320
Kluay's doing well.
Still the same as always.

393
00:33:16,400 --> 00:33:18,680
Oh, Mr. Sarut, I should get going now.

394
00:33:18,760 --> 00:33:20,440
Wait, wait, Mr. Warat.

395
00:33:21,640 --> 00:33:23,520
What about…

396
00:33:24,040 --> 00:33:28,160
about us being father and son…?

397
00:33:31,880 --> 00:33:35,680
I think we should stop
talking about the past.

398
00:33:41,920 --> 00:33:46,240
But I want to make things right.
I want a chance to take care of you,

399
00:33:46,320 --> 00:33:48,560
to be a good father.

400
00:33:48,640 --> 00:33:50,240
Can't you give me a chance?

401
00:33:52,080 --> 00:33:53,160
Mr. Sarut,

402
00:33:55,400 --> 00:33:56,800
I only have one father.

403
00:33:58,520 --> 00:33:59,800
His name is Wichan.

404
00:34:03,680 --> 00:34:05,600
But you've never even given me a chance.

405
00:34:06,120 --> 00:34:07,840
Can't you give me a chance?

406
00:34:08,360 --> 00:34:11,120
- Please.
- I think you already had that chance.

407
00:34:13,520 --> 00:34:15,560
When my mother needed you,

408
00:34:17,719 --> 00:34:19,480
my father, Mr. Wichan,

409
00:34:20,360 --> 00:34:22,239
stepped up in your place.

410
00:34:24,639 --> 00:34:27,159
All those years…

411
00:34:31,080 --> 00:34:33,199
when I needed someone,

412
00:34:34,600 --> 00:34:37,480
where were you?
Where did you disappear to?

413
00:34:39,400 --> 00:34:41,480
But everything I did,

414
00:34:42,000 --> 00:34:45,440
I did it for you.
I wanted you to have a good life.

415
00:34:50,320 --> 00:34:52,080
That's the price you have to pay.

416
00:34:54,440 --> 00:34:56,480
If you really want to do something for me,

417
00:34:58,560 --> 00:35:00,560
then from now on,

418
00:35:02,960 --> 00:35:04,920
let's just be acquaintances.

419
00:35:06,120 --> 00:35:09,000
I'll respect you as an elder.

420
00:35:11,080 --> 00:35:12,840
We owe each other nothing anymore.

421
00:35:19,560 --> 00:35:20,720
I'm sorry.

422
00:35:21,440 --> 00:35:22,480
Can you forgive me?

423
00:35:22,560 --> 00:35:24,520
Please don't
use the word "son," Mr. Sarut.

424
00:35:27,600 --> 00:35:29,600
Someone who never acted for their child,

425
00:35:33,520 --> 00:35:35,320
who never really cared for another person,

426
00:35:36,880 --> 00:35:38,240
has no right to call someone

427
00:35:38,920 --> 00:35:40,400
their child.

428
00:35:42,560 --> 00:35:43,880
I'll be going now.

429
00:35:44,680 --> 00:35:45,600
Take care.

430
00:35:46,280 --> 00:35:48,080
Son. My son.

431
00:35:49,160 --> 00:35:50,240
Son.

432
00:36:14,200 --> 00:36:16,400
Kluay, are you ready?

433
00:36:17,800 --> 00:36:18,800
Yes.

434
00:36:23,520 --> 00:36:25,760
Do you think Mom is still around here?

435
00:36:26,760 --> 00:36:28,480
She's probably still watching over us.

436
00:36:30,800 --> 00:36:33,680
Ever since that day,
I haven't seen her again.

437
00:36:36,360 --> 00:36:37,880
That's how parents are.

438
00:36:39,400 --> 00:36:40,480
What do you mean?

439
00:36:41,520 --> 00:36:43,760
Once they've taken care
of us to a certain point…

440
00:36:49,640 --> 00:36:52,720
They have to let us grow on our own.

441
00:36:52,800 --> 00:36:53,840
Right?

442
00:36:56,360 --> 00:36:58,600
Thank you, Mom,

443
00:36:58,680 --> 00:37:00,920
for always taking care of me.

444
00:37:01,800 --> 00:37:04,040
You don't have to worry anymore.

445
00:37:04,800 --> 00:37:07,560
I promise I'll take good care of myself.

446
00:37:09,240 --> 00:37:12,560
Now I have Grandma, Mr. Warat,

447
00:37:13,880 --> 00:37:15,960
Mama Toi, and Som.

448
00:37:17,240 --> 00:37:19,480
I have a good family now.

449
00:37:21,080 --> 00:37:23,520
You don't need to
worry about anything anymore.

450
00:37:27,360 --> 00:37:29,320
Thank you, Mom,

451
00:37:31,720 --> 00:37:33,320
for taking care of me since I was little

452
00:37:34,400 --> 00:37:35,960
as if I were your own son.

453
00:37:41,680 --> 00:37:42,880
As for Kluay,

454
00:37:44,760 --> 00:37:46,400
please don't worry.

455
00:37:47,840 --> 00:37:50,000
I promise I'll take care of her

456
00:37:50,840 --> 00:37:52,440
and love her with all my heart.

457
00:37:54,360 --> 00:37:55,720
I'll never let her

458
00:37:56,440 --> 00:37:57,960
be hurt again.

459
00:38:02,560 --> 00:38:05,160
Please rest peacefully up there, Mom.

460
00:38:34,160 --> 00:38:35,360
Let's go.

461
00:38:37,560 --> 00:38:40,680
THE END

462
00:41:03,200 --> 00:41:05,320
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
